<item>
            <title>[LU-16410] sanity-lfsck may leave lost+found folder in uncleaned state</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16410</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It was noticed that after execution sanity-lfsck tests .lustre/lost+found/ folder may be left in non-cleaned state. The script has an ending to do the clean up&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
cleanup the system at last
REFORMAT=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;yes&quot;&lt;/span&gt; cleanup_and_setup_lustre
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But probably this sometimes is not executed (test interrupted ?). I tried a few (for example test_1b, test_18c) and if the test is interrupted I see .lustre/lost+found/MDTxxxx/ and a number of files.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As a result a consequent test if it does not do the complete reformat may fail. Specifically sanity-lipe-find3 tests fail because it finds unexpected files in .lustre/lost+found/&lt;/p&gt;</description>
